'''Moderates in Revolution''' ({{lang-it|Moderati in Rivoluzione}}, MIR) is a political association founded in 2012 by the lawyer, banker and entrepreneur [[Gianpiero Samorì]].

In the [[2013 Italian general election|2013 general election]] the party presented its lists in the [[Centre-right coalition]] and obtained the 0.24% of the vote for the Chamber of Deputies and the 0.22% of the vote for the Senate, gaining no seats.

In May [[Walter Ferrazza]], a MIR member, was nominated Undersecretary in the [[Letta Cabinet]].

On 29 November 2013 MIR became an associate party of [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]]<ref>[http://goodmorningumbria.wordpress.com/2013/12/06/i-moderati-in-rivoluzione-confermano-ladesione-a-forza-italia/ I Moderati in Rivoluzione confermano l’adesione a Forza Italia]</ref> and Walter Ferrazza resigned as Undersecretary, because FI was passed to the opposition.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.it/2013/12/02/ferrazza-dimissioni-sottosegretario_n_4370924.html Walter Ferrazza dimissioni: il sottosegretario agli Affari regionali lascia il governo]</ref>

MIR and [[Renaissance (political party)|Renaissance]], the party led by [[Vittorio Sgarbi]] formed a joint list which ran its own candidates in the [[2018 Italian general election]] in the constituency of [[Friuli-Venezia Giulia]], gaining a few hundred votes (less than 0.1% for both the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]<ref>[http://elezioni.interno.gov.it/camera/scrutini/20180304/scrutiniCI09000000000 Ministero dell'Interno - Portale Eligendo]</ref> and the [[Senate (Italy)|Senate]]<ref>[http://elezioni.interno.gov.it/senato/scrutini/20180304/scrutiniSI06100000000 Ministero dell'Interno - Portale Eligendo]</ref>).

